Laboratory Reservation and Utilization System  
* Laboratory Room / Equipment booking  
* Conflict detection  
* Utilization reports  
* Schedule optimization 
USER ROLES 
1.1 Student / Faculty User 
• Submit reservation requests  
• Check real-time availability  
• View reservation status  
• Receive email notifications  
1.2 Administrator / Laboratory Coordinator 
• Approve or reject reservations  
• View all schedules  
• Monitor conflicts  
• Access utilization reports and dashboard 
REQUIREMENTS NEEDED 
1. The system must allow users to: 
• Select laboratory room or equipment  
• Input reservation details:  
o Name  
o Email  
o Section / Department  
o Date  
o Start time  
o End time  
o Purpose of use  
• Submit reservation request via web interface  
• Store all data in a centralized database 
2. The system must enforce laboratory operating hours: 
7:00 AM to 10:00 PM only 
The system must: 
• Reject reservations outside this time range  
• Ensure:  
o Start time ≥ 7:00 AM  
o End time ≤ 10:00 PM  
• Display error message: 
“Reservation is only allowed from 7:00 AM to 10:00 PM.” 
3. Real-Time Availability Checking 
The system must: 
• Check availability BEFORE submission  
• Validate:  
o Lab Room  
o Date  
o Time range  
• Display instant feedback:  
o “Available”  
o “Not Available (Already Reserved)”  
• Prevent submission if slot is unavailable 
4. Conflict Detection 
The system must: 
• Detect overlapping schedules  
• Compare:  
o Same laboratory room  
o Same date  
o Overlapping time intervals  
• Prevent double booking  
• Automatically mark conflicting reservations as:  
o Rejected or blocked 
5. Approval Workflow System 
The system must support: 
• Initial status: Pending  
• Admin-controlled status update:  
o Approved  
o Rejected  
• Automatic email notification upon status change  
6. Utilization Reports (DASHBOARD) 
The system must generate reports showing: 
• Total number of reservations  
• Approved vs Rejected vs Pending requests  
• Most used laboratory rooms  
• Frequency of usage per time slot  
• Daily, weekly, and monthly trends  
7. Schedule Optimization Support 
The system should: 
• Identify available time slots  
• Highlight peak usage hours  
• Suggest less congested schedules  
• Improve laboratory resource allocation 
SYSTEM INTERFACE REQUIREMENTS 
The system must include: 
• Web-based reservation form (frontend)  
• Real-time availability checker  
• Admin approval interface  
• Dashboard for utilization reports  
• Status display (Available / Pending / Approved / Rejected) 


